groupQpArray5[1]='<div id="quizpopper14"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 6</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f14"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>Below are some statements regarding international students. Select all the statements that are true for international students in general.</p></legend></div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-m-answer-instruction">[mark all correct answers]</div><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="a" id="q14a"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">a.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14a"><p>Academically, students arrive with positive and confident personal expectations of success.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="b" id="q14b"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">b.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14b"><p>The minority of the international students expect a rewarding and enriching experience.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="c" id="q14c"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">c.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14c"><p>All international students receive family support, both economic and psychological.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="d" id="q14d"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">d.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14d"><p>International students perceive career development and job preparation as one of their important needs.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="e" id="q14e"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">e.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14e"><p>All international students are confident about their English speaking and writing skills.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q14" value="f" id="q14f"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">f.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q14f"><p>International students are allowed to work in this country even outside of the campus environment.</p></label></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done14"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed14"></div></div></div>';
groupQpArray5[2]='<div id="quizpopper24"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 2</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f24"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>International students represent added value to your courses and other students as they can share a multicultural perspective of the world without having to travel to all those destinations.</p></legend></div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-t-f-cell-left"><input type="radio" name="q24" value="true" id="q24a"></div><div class="qp-t-f-cell-right"><label for="q24a"><span class="qp-t-f-answer">True</span></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-t-f-cell-left"><input type="radio" name="q24" value="false" id="q24b"></div><div class="qp-t-f-cell-right"><label for="q24b"><span class="qp-t-f-answer">False</span></label></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done24"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed24"></div></div></div>';
groupQpArray5[3]='<div id="quizpopper16"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 10</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f16"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>You have some international students in your class. Each of then is from a different country, and it is their first semester in the States. What are some of the practical tips that may help faculty understand and educate them better in their classes? Select all that apply.</p></legend></div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-m-answer-instruction">[mark all correct answers]</div><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="a" id="q16a"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">a.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16a"><p>Avoid interpreting their low engagement as disengagement because they may need to absorb the information before they feel confident to speak up.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="b" id="q16b"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">b.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16b"><p>Assigns students to groups so that international students are not picked last by their peers due to their language challenges.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="c" id="q16c"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">c.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16c"><p>Keep saying, &quot;Your English is already really good.&quot; This will encourage them.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="d" id="q16d"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">d.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16d"><p>Using Universal Design Principles, you can promote language learning by providing closed captions and transcripts for presentations, video, lectures, etc.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="e" id="q16e"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">e.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16e"><p>You do not have to discuss academic integrity policies in detail because all country have same levels of expectations.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="f" id="q16f"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">f.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16f"><p>You can provide audio and visual supplemental materials to help students understand concepts and improve their English listening and speaking skills.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="g" id="q16g"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">g.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16g"><p>Clarifying American pop culture references for international students is not important because they all already know what you are referring to.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="h" id="q16h"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">h.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16h"><p>You should use both synchronous and asynchronous communication tools.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="i" id="q16i"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">i.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16i"><p>You do not have to learn the names of international students.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q16" value="j" id="q16j"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">j.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q16j"><p>Incorporate cultural differences into instruction and turn them into teachable moments.</p></label></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done16"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed16"></div></div></div>';


