groupQpArray6[1]='<div id="quizpopper20"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 4</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f20"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>Match some of the disabilities with its example.</p></legend></div><div class="hideqpstuff">The task is to match the lettered items with the correct numbered items. Appearing below is a list of lettered items. Following that is a list of numbered items. Each numbered item is followed by a drop-down. Select the letter in the drop down that best matches the numbered item with the lettered alternatives.</div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-matching-item-container"><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">a.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><p>dyslexia, dysgraphia</p></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">b.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><p>congenital heart failure, rheumatoid arthritis, fibromyalgia, psoriasis</p></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">c.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><p>wheelchair-bound, CP that involves hands, fingers, mobility issues as well as permanent injuries</p></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">d.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><p>depression, anxiety</p></div></div></div></div><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">1.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><label for="q20_1"><p>Learning Disability</p></label></div><div class="qp-match-cell-right"><select class="form-control qp-select" name="q20_1" id="q20_1"><option>a</option><option>b</option><option>c</option><option>d</option></select></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">2.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><label for="q20_2"><p>Physical Disability</p></label></div><div class="qp-match-cell-right"><select class="form-control qp-select" name="q20_2" id="q20_2"><option>a</option><option>b</option><option>c</option><option>d</option></select></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">3.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><label for="q20_3"><p>Chronic Medical Conditions</p></label></div><div class="qp-match-cell-right"><select class="form-control qp-select" name="q20_3" id="q20_3"><option>a</option><option>b</option><option>c</option><option>d</option></select></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-match-cell-left">4.</div><div class="qp-match-cell-middle"><label for="q20_4"><p>Psychological Disability</p></label></div><div class="qp-match-cell-right"><select class="form-control qp-select" name="q20_4" id="q20_4"><option>a</option><option>b</option><option>c</option><option>d</option></select></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done20"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed20"></div></div></div>';
groupQpArray6[2]='<div id="quizpopper17"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 2</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f17"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>Is the statement below true or false?</p><p>Not all students who identify and register with Student Services use the accommodation(s) for which they qualify during their academic career at ISU?</p></legend></div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-t-f-cell-left"><input type="radio" name="q17" value="true" id="q17a"></div><div class="qp-t-f-cell-right"><label for="q17a"><span class="qp-t-f-answer">True</span></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-t-f-cell-left"><input type="radio" name="q17" value="false" id="q17b"></div><div class="qp-t-f-cell-right"><label for="q17b"><span class="qp-t-f-answer">False</span></label></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done17"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed17"></div></div></div>';
groupQpArray6[3]='<div id="quizpopper18"><div class="qpqvalue">Value: 10</div><div class="qpq"><form class="qp-form" name="f18"><fieldset><div class="qp-the-question"><legend><p>Jeanette, Nicole, Kevin, Hillary and Brady are some of your students in your class. Jeanette and Nicole have intellectual disabilities; they have a paraprofessional who accompanies them to selected regular education classrooms, providing instructional support. Nicole is identified with socio-emotional disability and receives special education services for both language arts and mathematics. Kevin is diagnosed with autism, exhibits difficulties in social skills, and is high functioning cognitively. Hillary and Brady have specific learning disabilities and receive special education services for both language arts and mathematics.</p><p>What are some of the practical tips that you can use in your class to make learning easier for them and some other disabled students?</p></legend></div><div class="qpindent"><div class="qp-m-answer-instruction">[mark all correct answers]</div><div class="qp-table"><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="a" id="q18a"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">a.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18a"><p>Connect with disabled students enrolled in your courses and ask them about their preferred instructional/learning strategies.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="b" id="q18b"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">b.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18b"><p>Regarding course materials, consider colors, fonts, and formats that are easily viewed by students with low vision or a form of color blindness and avoid using websites that have several flash-based visuals that may cause seizure.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="c" id="q18c"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">c.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18c"><p>Post course materials, assignments, and deadlines with advanced notice because it allows students time to plan for accommodations and workload.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="d" id="q18d"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">d.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18d"><p>Use multiple formats for instruction for delivering content because students learn different ways. You can make outlines or recordings available online or explain in a video all printed assignments.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="e" id="q18e"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">e.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18e"><p>Prepare alternative assignments because some students may have difficulties with the requested method of delivery such as presentation and public speaking.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="f" id="q18f"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">f.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18f"><p>Think of multiple ways students may be able to participate without feeling excluded instead of assuming what activities they can or cannot do.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="g" id="q18g"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">g.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18g"><p>Remove negative portrayals of the members of the disabled population.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="h" id="q18h"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">h.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18h"><p>Encourage students to hide their disabilities at Student Disability Services.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="i" id="q18i"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">i.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18i"><p>Make disabled students feel like any other student by using positive reinforcement and giving them personalized attention during the learning process.</p></label></div></div><div class="qp-row"><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-left"><input type="checkbox" name="q18" value="j" id="q18j"></div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-middle">j.</div><div class="qp-m-answer-cell-right"><label for="q18j"><p>Follow universal design principles and create assessments that offer options for demonstrating relevant knowledge and skills. Let students choose the method to deliver their representative project.</p></label></div></div></div></div></fieldset></form><div class="collapse qpqfeedback" id="f_done18"></div><div class="collapse qpqfeedback2" id="feed18"></div></div></div>';

